no existence of a winding number.

2481
01:49:30,520 --> 01:49:33,520
A winding number or a particle with a winding number?

2482
01:49:33,520 --> 01:49:35,520
A particle with a winding number.

2483
01:49:35,520 --> 01:49:37,520
You can make them.

2484
01:49:37,520 --> 01:49:39,520
I'll show you how to make them.

2485
01:49:47,520 --> 01:49:49,520
We do have to start with something.

2486
01:49:52,520 --> 01:49:54,020
So we start with a

2487
01:49:54,020 --> 01:49:55,520
particle which has no winding number.

2488
01:49:55,520 --> 01:49:57,520
That's a little string that looks like that.

2489
01:49:57,520 --> 01:49:58,520
Okay?

2490
01:49:58,520 --> 01:49:59,520
Now we take this,

2491
01:49:59,520 --> 01:50:01,520
and we pull it around,

2492
01:50:01,520 --> 01:50:03,520
we stretch it out.

2493
01:50:03,520 --> 01:50:06,520
It's still got no winding number.

2494
01:50:06,520 --> 01:50:08,520
It's not wound around the thing.

2495
01:50:08,520 --> 01:50:11,520
And now we stretch it all the way around here

2496
01:50:11,520 --> 01:50:13,520
so that it comes back the back side

2497
01:50:17,520 --> 01:50:19,520
and comes up over here.

2498
01:50:22,520 --> 01:50:24,520
Can you see what I've done?

2499
01:50:24,520 --> 01:50:26,520
It still has no winding number.

2500
01:50:26,520 --> 01:50:29,520
The winding number of this piece is canceled out.

2501
01:50:29,520 --> 01:50:31,520
It's canceled out by the winding number of that piece.

2502
01:50:31,520 --> 01:50:33,520
So you take your arm,

2503
01:50:33,520 --> 01:50:35,520
you take the rubber band,

2504
01:50:35,520 --> 01:50:37,520
and you pull it around,

2505
01:50:37,520 --> 01:50:40,520
and then take the two pieces here.

2506
01:50:40,520 --> 01:50:42,520
And that's what you're left with.

2507
01:50:42,520 --> 01:50:44,520
That still has no winding number.

2508
01:50:44,520 --> 01:50:46,520
But remember now that in string theory,

2509
01:50:46,520 --> 01:50:49,520
the basic process of interaction is for things like this

2510
01:50:49,520 --> 01:50:51,520
to become things like this.

2511
01:50:51,520 --> 01:50:53,520
Rearrangement.

2512
01:50:53,520 --> 01:50:55,520
So if you sit there for a while,

2513
01:50:55,520 --> 01:50:57,520
this string will rearrange and form that.

2514
01:50:57,520 --> 01:51:00,520
Now what does this have?

2515
01:51:00,520 --> 01:51:04,520
It has two particles with opposite winding number.

2516
01:51:04,520 --> 01:51:06,520
Okay?

2517
01:51:06,520 --> 01:51:09,520
We still have a net zero winding number.

2518
01:51:09,520 --> 01:51:10,520
One is wound one way,

2519
01:51:10,520 --> 01:51:12,520
one is wound the other way.

2520
01:51:12,520 --> 01:51:14,520
But now they're disconnected,

2521
01:51:14,520 --> 01:51:16,520
and they're free to separate.

2522
01:51:19,520 --> 01:51:21,520
Throw that one away.

2523
01:51:21,520 --> 01:51:23,520
Just eject it out of the system.

2524
01:51:23,520 --> 01:51:25,520
Give it some velocity.

2525
01:51:25,520 --> 01:51:27,520
And when it gets off to alpha centauri,

2526
01:51:27,520 --> 01:51:28,520
you forget about it,

2527
01:51:28,520 --> 01:51:31,520
and you're left with a particle with winding number.

2528
01:51:34,520 --> 01:51:37,520
So whether you like them or not,

2529
01:51:37,520 --> 01:51:39,520
you can't forbid them.

2530
01:51:39,520 --> 01:51:41,520
Some things you can try to forbid.

2531
01:51:41,520 --> 01:51:43,520
You can say if they're not there to begin with,

2532
01:51:43,520 --> 01:51:45,520
they'll never be there.

2533
01:51:45,520 --> 01:51:47,520
Possibly.

2534
01:51:47,520 --> 01:51:49,520
Some things you can't forbid

2535
01:51:49,520 --> 01:51:51,520
because you can imagine

2536
01:51:51,520 --> 01:51:53,520
that the processes of the theory itself,

2537
01:51:53,520 --> 01:51:55,520
the important processes in the theory,

2538
01:51:55,520 --> 01:51:57,520
can force them on you,

2539
01:51:57,520 --> 01:51:59,520
and these get forced on you.

2540
01:51:59,520 --> 01:52:01,520
Of course, they always get forced in pairs.

2541
01:52:01,520 --> 01:52:03,520
But you can...

2542
01:52:03,520 --> 01:52:05,520
That's...

2543
01:52:05,520 --> 01:52:07,520
You throw away half of them

2544
01:52:07,520 --> 01:52:09,520
and just do some experiments

2545
01:52:09,520 --> 01:52:11,520
with the remaining ones.

2546
01:52:11,520 --> 01:52:14,520
And this is with increasing energy,

2547
01:52:14,520 --> 01:52:16,520
I guess, then?

2548
01:52:16,520 --> 01:52:20,520
The Kaluzik-Klein closed string gets larger?

2549
01:52:20,520 --> 01:52:22,520
Does that be more energy?

2550
01:52:22,520 --> 01:52:23,520
Yeah, it does.

2551
01:52:23,520 --> 01:52:25,520
It gets some energy not only from momentum,

2552
01:52:25,520 --> 01:52:26,520
but from being stretched.

2553
01:52:26,520 --> 01:52:28,520
It takes energy to do it.

2554
01:52:30,520 --> 01:52:32,520
But you know, this is the sort of thing

2555
01:52:32,520 --> 01:52:34,520
which would happen if you collided

2556
01:52:34,520 --> 01:52:37,520
two particles with no winding number,

2557
01:52:37,520 --> 01:52:39,520
just two Kaluzik-Klein particles.

2558
01:52:39,520 --> 01:52:41,520
You collide them hard.

2559
01:52:41,520 --> 01:52:44,520
Every possible combination of stuff happens.

2560
01:52:44,520 --> 01:52:46,520
And among the things which would happen

2561
01:52:46,520 --> 01:52:48,520
is these winding and anti-winding things

2562
01:52:48,520 --> 01:52:50,520
would go flying off.

2563
01:52:52,520 --> 01:52:54,520
And the logic is the same as the logic

2564
01:52:54,520 --> 01:52:56,520
of electric charge.

2565
01:52:56,520 --> 01:52:58,520
So, if you started with no electric charge,

2566
01:52:58,520 --> 01:53:00,520
does that mean there would be no electrons?

2567
01:53:00,520 --> 01:53:01,520
No.

2568
01:53:01,520 --> 01:53:03,520
Any kind of collision that would take place

2569
01:53:03,520 --> 01:53:05,520
would create electrons and positrons,

2570
01:53:05,520 --> 01:53:07,520
and then the positrons could go flying off

2571
01:53:07,520 --> 01:53:09,520
to some other place,

2572
01:53:09,520 --> 01:53:12,520
and you'd be left with electrons.

2573
01:53:12,520 --> 01:53:14,520
So the logic is really no different

2574
01:53:14,520 --> 01:53:16,520
than electric charge.

2575
01:53:16,520 --> 01:53:18,520
You can't not have electric charge

2576
01:53:18,520 --> 01:53:21,520
because you can always make it in pairs.

2577
01:53:22,520 --> 01:53:24,520
The net charge in the world

2578
01:53:24,520 --> 01:53:26,520
might be zero, for all we know.

2579
01:53:26,520 --> 01:53:32,520
The net winding number might be zero,

2580
01:53:32,520 --> 01:53:34,520
but who cares?

2581
01:53:34,520 --> 01:53:40,520
We can do experiments on a region

2582
01:53:40,520 --> 01:53:42,520
which contains a winding number.

2583
01:53:42,520 --> 01:53:44,520
So, yeah.

2584
01:53:44,520 --> 01:53:47,520
This has a name, incidentally.

2585
01:53:47,520 --> 01:53:50,520
The equivalence between theories

2586
01:53:50,520 --> 01:53:52,520
which look different

2587
01:53:52,520 --> 01:53:55,520
usually called a duality.

2588
01:53:56,520 --> 01:53:59,520
This is called T-duality.

2589
01:53:59,520 --> 01:54:02,520
Capital T-duality.

2590
01:54:02,520 --> 01:54:05,520
And the T in this case stands for torus.

2591
01:54:07,520 --> 01:54:09,520
T stands for torus.

2592
01:54:09,520 --> 01:54:12,520
This is torus duality, or T-duality.

2593
01:54:12,520 --> 01:54:15,520
And as I say, it's a duality which relates

2594
01:54:15,520 --> 01:54:18,520
compactifications on very small geometries

2595
01:54:18,520 --> 01:54:20,520
to compactifications on big geometries.

2596
01:54:20,520 --> 01:54:22,520
And it's a rather startling thing.

2597
01:54:22,520 --> 01:54:24,520
I mean, when it was first discovered,

2598
01:54:24,520 --> 01:54:26,520
it surprised everybody.

2599
01:54:26,520 --> 01:54:28,520
Good.

2600
01:54:28,520 --> 01:54:32,520
What it means is that geometry defined

2601
01:54:32,520 --> 01:54:35,520
in terms of how strings...

2602
01:54:35,520 --> 01:54:39,520
Geometry can often be recovered

2603
01:54:39,520 --> 01:54:41,520
or partly recovered

2604
01:54:41,520 --> 01:54:46,520
from the spectrum of modes on a...

2605
01:54:46,520 --> 01:54:48,520
The geometry of a drum head,

2606
01:54:48,520 --> 01:54:49,520
the shape of a drum head.

2607
01:54:49,520 --> 01:54:51,520
This is a famous mathematical question.

2608
01:54:51,520 --> 01:54:54,520
Can the shape of a drum head

2609
01:54:54,520 --> 01:54:56,520
be predicted from the sound of it?

2610
01:54:56,520 --> 01:54:57,520
The sound that it makes,

2611
01:54:57,520 --> 01:54:59,520
from the spectrum of vibrations?

2612
01:54:59,520 --> 01:55:01,520
The answer is not quite,

2613
01:55:01,520 --> 01:55:03,520
but you can predict a lot of the shape

2614
01:55:03,520 --> 01:55:05,520
of the drum head.

2615
01:55:05,520 --> 01:55:07,520
The same question applies

2616
01:55:07,520 --> 01:55:09,520
to these compactifications.

2617
01:55:09,520 --> 01:55:11,520
From the spectrum of particles,

2618
01:55:11,520 --> 01:55:13,520
the spectrum of vibrational energies,

2619
01:55:13,520 --> 01:55:15,520
vibrational and other kinds of energies,

2620
01:55:15,520 --> 01:55:17,520
can you predict the shape

2621
01:55:17,520 --> 01:55:20,520
or the size of the compact directions?

2622
01:55:20,520 --> 01:55:23,520
And the answer is yes to a large extent.

2623
01:55:23,520 --> 01:55:25,520
But...

2624
01:55:25,520 --> 01:55:28,520
there are some ambiguities

2625
01:55:28,520 --> 01:55:30,520
and some dualities

2626
01:55:30,520 --> 01:55:33,520
that you can't tell if it's a tiny geometry

2627
01:55:33,520 --> 01:55:35,520
or if it's a big geometry

2628
01:55:35,520 --> 01:55:38,520
because these two go into each other.

2629
01:55:38,520 --> 01:55:40,520
That would not be the case

2630
01:55:40,520 --> 01:55:42,520
with a drum, I assure you.

2631
01:55:42,520 --> 01:55:44,520
Uh...

2632
01:55:44,520 --> 01:55:46,520
You would not mistake a small drum

2633
01:55:46,520 --> 01:55:48,520
for a big drum.

2634
01:55:48,520 --> 01:55:50,520
Okay, good.

2635
01:55:50,520 --> 01:55:53,520
For more, please visit us at

2636
01:55:53,520 --> 01:55:54,520
stanford.edu.

2637
01:55:55,520 --> 01:55:55,793
Thank you.

